pageContext.claim: “It’s terrible. And what Strzok did -- and don’t forget: he was with Bob Muller for over a year. Somebody said fired. Well he fired because they found out.”
pageContext.analysis: FBI agent Peter Strzok sent anti-Trump text messages in 2016 and was criticized by the Justice Department's inspector general. But the IG report also found that no improper biases or considerations went into the FBI's decision making in 2016. In any case, Strzok worked on special counsel Robert Mueller's team for two months in 2017, not "over a year."
